<div class="home-hero">
  <div class="home-hero-content">
    <h1>BodMetriks</h1>
    <p class="home-subtitle">
      Track body measurements, progress photos, and check-ins over time so you can better understand your fitness journey.
    </p>

    <div class="home-actions">
      <%= link_to "View Public Profiles", profiles_path, class: "button-link" %>
      <%= link_to "Sign Up", signup_path, class: "button-link" %>

    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="home-grid">
  <section class="info-card">
    <h2>What this app does</h2>
    <p>
      BodMetriks helps users record physical progress over time through profiles, check-ins, body measurements, and optional progress photos.
    </p>
    <p>
      It is designed to make it easier to review changes across different body parts and monitor trends through reports and exports.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="info-card">
    <h2>How to use the site</h2>
    <ol class="info-list">
      <li>Create a profile to begin tracking progress.</li>
      <li>Add check-ins over time with notes and optional progress photos.</li>
      <li>Record measurements for body parts such as waist, chest, shoulders, and weight.</li>
      <li>Use the progress report page to review trends by body part and timeframe.</li>
      <li>Export report data as CSV when needed.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="info-card">
    <h2>What you can track</h2>
    <ul class="info-list">
      <li>Check-in dates and notes</li>
      <li>Body part measurements</li>
      <li>Front, back and side body progress photos</li>
      <li>Measurement-specific body part photos</li>
      <li>Measurement history and summary reports</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</div>